main event: A civilian observed an unidentified object in the sky over Sequoia National Park, California in August 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed on multiple nights from August 24-27, 1965.
The object was seen moving rapidly from northwest to southeast, changing color and direction at times.
The object was brighter and moved faster than known satellites.
The Air Force investigated the sighting and could not identify the object as a known satellite.
Another witness also reported seeing 4 luminous objects behaving similarly in the sky during the same time period.
sighted object: a bright, fast-moving object that changed color and direction
witnesses: a civilian and a group of 5 friends
